         <abstract>
            <p>The inversive congruential method with prime modulus for generating uniform pseudorandom numbers has several very promising properties. Very recently, a generalization for composite moduli has been introduced. In the present paper it is shown that the generated sequences have very attractive statistical independence properties.</p>
          </abstract>
